What is the purpose of an abstract? 

•	 A stand alone, mini-version of the 
paper (250 words or less). 
•	 Describes the main sections of the 
paper. 
•	 States the purpose, findings, and 
impact of the work. 
•	 The goal is an economy of words. 

The Essentials of an Abstract 
from the UW Madison Writing Center 

In an abstracts you address this question: 
– What is the report about, in miniature and

without too much detail?

By doing the following 
– State main objectives: What did you

investigate? Why?

– Describe methods: What did you use? 
– Summarize the most important results: What 
did you find out? 
– State major conclusions and significance: What 
do your results mean? So what?) 

